The paper discusses the use of smart ants as intelligent agents for efficient routing in wireless mesh networks, which involves concepts related to network infrastructure (NI) and data structures (DS). The use of biologically inspired agents also suggests a connection to the field of multi-agent systems (MA) and artificial intelligence (AI). Additionally, the paper proposes a distributed interference-aware data forwarding algorithm, which involves information theory (IT) concepts. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NI, followed by cs.DS, cs.MA, cs.AI, and cs.IT.
